summary:
The Security Council,

Reaffirming its relevant resolutions, 
Guided by the purposes and principles of the Charter of the United Nations, 
Reaffirming Israel's obligation to abide by its legal obligations under the Fourth Geneva Convention, 
Condemning measures aimed at altering the demographic composition of the Palestinian Territory, 
Expressing grave concern over Israeli settlement activities, 
Recalling obligations under the Quartet Roadmap, 

1. Reaffirms that Israel's settlements in the occupied Palestinian territory have no legal validity and constitute a flagrant violation under international law; 
2. Demands Israel immediately and completely cease all settlement activities; 
3. Underlines that it will not recognize changes to the 4 June 1967 lines, except those agreed by the parties through negotiations; 
4. Stresses cessation of settlement activities is essential for the two-State solution; 
5. Calls upon States to distinguish between Israel and the occupied territories; 
6. Calls for steps to prevent violence against civilians, and for compliance with international law; 
7. Calls upon both parties to act on international law, observe calm and restraint, and refrain from provocative actions; 
8. Calls upon parties to launch credible negotiations on all final status issues.
The Security Council:

9. Urges intensification and acceleration of international and regional diplomatic efforts to achieve a comprehensive, just and lasting peace in the Middle East, based on relevant UN resolutions, Madrid terms of reference, the Arab Peace Initiative, and the Quartet Roadmap, and an end to the Israeli occupation that began in 1967;

10. Confirms its determination to support the parties throughout negotiations and implementation of an agreement;

11. Reaffirms its determination to examine practical ways to secure full implementation of its relevant resolutions;

12. Requests the Secretary-General to report to the Council every three months on implementation of the present resolution;

13. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
